#: ../../users_databases.rst:5
msgid "Users databases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:7
msgid ""
"NethSecurity introduces support for two types of users databases: a local"
" database and a remote LDAP database, enhancing user management "
"capabilities. Users inside the databases can be used for VPN connections,"
" including the :ref:`openvpn_roadwarrior-section`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:10
msgid ""
"Only users with a password can connect to VPN by authenticating with a "
"username and password. Users without a password can connect to VPN by "
"authenticating with a certificate or other authentication methods."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:14
msgid "Local database"
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:16
msgid ""
"The local user database is an inherent component of the firewall, "
"ensuring seamless user authentication for VPN services. It is present by "
"default, offering a foundation for user management."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:19
msgid ""
"To create a new user, click on the :guilabel:`Add user` button to "
"initiate the process. When configuring a local user, you should fill all "
"the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:22
msgid "``Username``: specifies the desired username."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:23
msgid ""
"``Display Name``: specifies the display name of the user. This field is "
"optional."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:24
msgid ""
"``User password``: specifies the password of the user. This is required "
"only if the VPN is configured to use password authentication."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:25
msgid ""
"``Confirm password``: specifies the password of the user, make sure to "
"match the password with the one specified in the previous field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:27
msgid ""
"The local user database is implemented as UCI configuration file. "
"Paswords of local users are stored in the Unix passwd format, ensuring "
"compatibility and security in the local user database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:31
msgid "Remote databases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:33
msgid ""
"The adminsitrator can extend the capabilities of the firewall by adding "
"new remote databases. Users in remote databases must be added directly at"
" the source. User modifications should be made on the underlying LDAP "
"server to accurately reflect changes in the firewall configuration page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:37
msgid ""
"If the remote database is offline, VPN authentication will fail. It is "
"crucial to ensure that the remote database is online and accessible to "
"ensure proper user authentication through the VPN service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:40
msgid ""
"When configuring a remote database, click on the :guilabel:`Add database`"
" button  and fill all the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:42
msgid ""
"``LDAP URI``: specifies the LDAP Uniform Resource Identifier (URI), "
"including the server address and port (e.g., ``ldap://example.com:389``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:44
msgid ""
"``Type``: specifies the type of LDAP server. The available options are "
"``Active Directory`` and ``OpenLDAP``. If OpenLDAP is selected, the "
"remote server should respect the RFC 2307 schema."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:47
msgid ""
"``Base DN``: specifies the LDAP Base Distinguished Name (DN), "
"representing the starting point for searches in the LDAP directory (eg. "
"``dc=example,dc=com``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:49
msgid ""
"``User DN``: specifies the LDAP User Distinguished Name (DN). If not "
"present, the default value is equal to base_dn (eg. "
"``cn=users,dc=example,dc=com``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:51
msgid ""
"``User attribute field``: specifies the user attribute used to identify "
"the user. For example, ``sAMAccountName`` for Active Directory or ``uid``"
" for OpenLDAP."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:53
msgid ""
"``User CN field``: specifies the user attribute containing the user's "
"complete name. For example, ``cn`` for nboth Active Directory and "
"OpenLDAP."
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:55
msgid ""
"``StartTLS``: enables StartTLS for secure communication with the LDAP "
"server"
msgstr ""

#: ../../users_databases.rst:57
msgid ""
"``Verify TLS certificate``: determines whether to enable or disable "
"certificate validation"
msgstr ""

